ðŸ“Š Result Summary
ï‚· Dynamic IP Assignment: All devices (PCs and phones) successfully obtained IP addresses from the correct
DHCP pool.
ï‚· Wireless Security: Devices could only connect with correct WPA2-PSK credentials.
ï‚· Inter-VLAN Routing: All departments could communicate as required.
ï‚· Access Point Connectivity: Each AP was reachable and bridged correctly to VLANs.
ï‚· Segmentation: Devices in one VLAN couldnâ€™t access other VLANs unless routing was enabled.
ï‚· Ping Tests: Latency was simulated, and all pings returned replies confirming end-to-end communication.
ï‚· Visualization: Packet Tracer visually confirmed all packets followed the expected path, respecting VLAN
tagging and trunk links.
